state.unicode: Agamemnon can demand tribute from his vassals. They will provide resources, but this will put a strain on his relations with them. The lower relations are with a vassal, the fewer resources they will be willing to provide.
Each turn your vassals will provide resources for you faction, but higher rates will cause negative diplomatic relations between you.

uientry.unicode: The resources collected from all of your vassals. Each turn they will provide resources for your faction, but higher rates will cause negative diplomatic relations between you. In turn, lower relations will cause your vassals to provide fewer resources.
Your vassals will provide resources, but if you increase tax rates, relations between you will worsen. In turn, lower relations will cause your vassals to provide fewer resources.

state.unicode: Choose a vassal and then a tribute to demand from them. Your vassals will reluctantly comply with demand. Although you will acquire resources, you will also lose some respect.

uientry.unicode: Left-click to select, double left-click to initiate diplomacy

state.unicode: Establish vassals to demand tribute from them.

uientry.unicode: Lord Agamemnon hungers for a grand feast! He demands an immediate tribute from his vassals to honour his might and greatness.
Agamemnon grows restless. The wanax demands wood to build great ships and arm his warriors with spears and arrows.
Lord Agamemnon demands that his vassals honour his divine rule. He expects a tribute of stone to erect statues and buildings for the ages.
Great Agamemnon will see his armies clad in the finest bronze. He demands from his vassals an immediate tribute of the precious metal.
The great king Agamemnon demands an offering of gold from his vassals in recognition of the wisdom and temperance of his rule.
